<a name="TOC-COVID-19-UPDATE---March-27-2020"></a><span style="color:rgb(0,0,0);font-size:large;font-family:Lucida Grande,Lucida Sans Unicode,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal">COVID-19 UPDATE - March 27, 2020</span>
</h4>
<div style="text-align:center"><span style="color:rgb(0,0,0);font-size:large;font-family:Lucida Grande,Lucida Sans Unicode,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1KwBMoKnrBG9i4QWSFCQPMg0-JZGiOb6y/view?usp=sharing" target="_blank">Emilie Knisley's 3-27-20 Letter to the OESU Community </a><br></span></div>
<div><span style="color:rgb(0,0,0);font-size:large;font-family:Lucida Grande,Lucida Sans Unicode,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal"><br></span></div>
<div style="text-align:center"><font color="#000000" size="3">The Governor has issued an <a href="https://governor.vermont.gov/sites/scott/files/documents/Directive%205%20-%20Continuity%20of%20Learning%20Planning%20_0.pdf" target="_blank">order</a> dismissing schools for in-person instruction for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. </font></div>
<div style="text-align:center"><font color="#000000" face="Lucida Grande, Lucida Sans Unicode, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif" size="3"><span>  </span></font></div>
<div style="text-align:center"><span style="color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:Lucida Grande,Lucida Sans Unicode,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:medium;background-color:transparent">Gov. Phil Scott's <a href="https://governor.vermont.gov/press-release/governor-phil-scott-dismisses-schools-person-instruction-remainder-2019-2020-school">press release</a>. </span></div>
<div><span style="color:rgb(0,0,0);font-size:large;font-family:Lucida Grande,Lucida Sans Unicode,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal"><br></span></div>
<font color="#444444" face="verdana, sans-serif" size="3">Gov. Phil Scott announced that the Vermont Department of Public Service has released an interactive Public Wi-Fi Hot Spot Map to help Vermonters connect to publicly available internet service during the COVID-19 pandemic. The map includes the location of the Wi-Fi hot spots and pertinent information about how to access them, including places where users can access Wi-Fi from outside the building or in a parked vehicle to encourage social distancing. <a href="https://vtpsd.maps.arcgis.com/apps/webappviewer/index.html?id=c926d155167d4a5586e8e1aca1701cfa" target="_blank">Here is a Link to the Public Hotspot Map</a>. Locally, you can access the Internet at the Waits River Valley School, the Blake Memorial Library, and the Corinth Town Hall.</font><p style="margin:0px 0px 15px;padding:0px;border:0px;outline:0px;background-color:transparent;font-family:Lucida Grande,Lucida Sans Unicode,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;text-align:center"><br></p>
<p style="margin:0px 0px 15px;padding:0px;border:0px;outline:0px;background-color:transparent;font-family:Lucida Grande,Lucida Sans Unicode,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;text-align:center"><font color="#000000"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1o0e3CTqcJBCpCxKNtntu9xdJSoBRR1bD/view?usp=sharing" target="_blank">OESU Superintendent of Schools, Emilie Knisley's Letter to the OESU Community</a><br></font></p>
